idance**\\n\\nI’m considering that the generated test scaffold might need agent guidance to prevent using an old interface for the `javac` issue. The existing tests will fail to compile without some updates. The setup categories also mention including other test code setups in the guidance. I’m thinking that \\\"other test-code setup\\\" could mean writing a temporary web app and using an ephemeral local server. The action should probably be \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" if guidance is there, but I should choose \\\"no_action\\\" unless extra setup is found necessary.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing webapp tests**\\n\\nI’m generating tests for a web application and need to create temp webapp descriptors, but that’s just normal test code. The generated tests already have a temp webapp, yet the WebAppClassLoader's custom context API has changed. These tests must implement the 9.4 interface, which fixes the compile issue, but it’s still about setup. I wonder if the library needs anything beyond the usual test scaffold for full coverage. I'll note potential risks related to optional modules, but additional setup isn't necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-webapp:9.4.0.RC1 is self-contained for meaningful embedded WebAppContext/WebAppClassLoader coverage through its normal transitive Jetty and javax.servlet dependencies; no extra Maven dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is concretely required.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported javac failure is caused by a Jetty 9.4 WebAppClassLoader.Context API change: isSystemClass/isServerClass now take Class<?> and the interface also requires isServerResource(String, URL) and isSystemResource(String, URL). This is a test-source compatibility fix, not setup.\",\n    \"Optional Jetty features such as JSP, JMX, annotations, JNDI, or deployment-manager scenarios may require additional Jetty modules, but they are not required for baseline meaningful coverage of jetty-webapp itself.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b7bfda586c6bbb2016a42995418fc8196b56df0fe1bc067c5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 807, "output": 958, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27365, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782749507687, "responseId": "resp_0b7bfda586c6bbb2016a4299441fb48196b56a2b67da6ea2d7"}, "toolResults": []}
